Key Match Events: Tunisia beat São Tomé e Principe 4-0 to take the lead of Group H.
Malawi won 1-0 against Liberia in Monrovia.
Pre-Game Insights: Tunisia, whom Malawi Flames meet on Tuesday at Bingu Stadium, are Group H favourites.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The top team from each group after Match Day 10 shall earn an automatic qualification for the 2026 World Cup finals.
The four best second-placed teams from all nine groups will engage in a continental playoff, determining a single victor who will then proceed to a second and final playoff.
The final stage will comprise six teams from various confederations, with the top two emerging as qualified participants, ultimately making up the 48 competing teams.
